# ⚙️ Project Overview

## 🔧 Testing Approach

The project involved durability testing of electric motors using controlled environments and repeated operation cycles.

## 🌡 Test Conditions

* Cold environment
* Ambient environment
* Hot environment
* Variable load conditions

## 🧪 Procedure

1. Motors were mounted on a test setup
2. Load was applied to simulate real usage
3. Motors were operated for multiple cycles
4. Performance behavior was monitored
5. Observations were recorded and compared

## 📈 Parameters Analyzed

* Current behavior
* Motion characteristics
* Response time
* Stability across cycles

## 🎯 Goal

To understand how motor performance changes under stress and identify reliability trends.
